; collision_layer = 2 (not 1): the navmesh bakes only layer-1 colliders
; (mountains / rivers / buildings / NavFloor), so trees on layer 2 are NOT
; punched out of the walkable mesh — units no longer route around whole
; forests. collision_mask = 0 means units pass through trunks freely.
; The pick raycast in camera_controller.gd queries all layers (it sets no
; collision_mask), so trees stay clickable and right-click-gatherable.
